207
00:11:38,810 --> 00:11:39,743
AIZAWA: Yes.

208
00:11:39,777 --> 00:11:41,077
But of course,
that alone doesn't

209
00:11:41,110 --> 00:11:42,410
come prove they were Kira.

210
00:11:42,443 --> 00:11:44,610
NEAR: And L was willing to
release them because of that?

211
00:11:44,643 --> 00:11:45,843
-No.

212
00:11:45,877 --> 00:11:48,010
L had Deputy Director
Yagami, the chief detective

213
00:11:48,043 --> 00:11:50,077
at the time, put on an act.

214
00:11:50,110 --> 00:11:52,477
He was instructed to tell the
suspects that they had both

215
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:55,210
been found guilty of being
Kira and the second Kira,

216
00:11:55,243 --> 00:11:57,810
and that they were
going to be executed.

217
00:11:57,843 --> 00:11:59,377
Then on the way,
the deputy director

218
00:11:59,410 --> 00:12:01,877
pulled over and pointed
a gun at the suspects.

219
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:04,243
He said that he would first
kill Kira, then himself.

220
00:12:06,843 --> 00:12:09,443
The idea was that
if he were Kira,

221
00:12:09,477 --> 00:12:14,243
the suspect would have killed
the chief right then and there.

222
00:12:14,277 --> 00:12:16,043
-(VOICEOVER) Kira
is quite impressive.

223
00:12:16,077 --> 00:12:20,010
He must have used his detainment
to demonstrate his innocence.

224
00:12:20,043 --> 00:12:21,743
Well done.

225
00:12:21,777 --> 00:12:23,677
Out of curiosity,
did the suspect

226
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:26,810
volunteer to be detained as
part of the investigation?

227
00:12:26,843 --> 00:12:28,177
-Hm.

228
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:31,177
Come to think of it, Light did
volunteer to be imprisoned.

229
00:12:33,877 --> 00:12:36,243
NEAR: If he did, then I'd
say that settles the matter.

230
00:12:36,277 --> 00:12:37,710
Wouldn't you?

231
00:12:37,743 --> 00:12:39,243
So, who was it?

232
00:12:39,277 --> 00:12:41,777
Who were those two suspects?

233
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:43,410
-I can't tell you that much.

234
00:12:43,443 --> 00:12:45,043
I'm willing to
cooperate, but I'm still

235
00:12:45,077 --> 00:12:49,043
a member of the Japanese
task force working under L.

236
00:12:49,077 --> 00:12:50,610
NEAR: I understand.

237
00:12:50,643 --> 00:12:52,477
Thank you very much.
you information's

238
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:55,610
been quite valuable, especially
the part about Shinigami's eyes

239
00:12:55,643 --> 00:12:58,010
that enable you to see
other peoples' names.

240
00:12:58,043 --> 00:12:59,443
It was very helpful.

241
00:12:59,477 --> 00:13:01,877
Goodbye.

242
00:13:01,910 --> 00:13:02,377
-Hm.

243
00:13:07,610 --> 00:13:09,243
RESTER: Will that
be enough, Near?

244
00:13:09,277 --> 00:13:11,610
Shouldn't you have pressed
for a little more information?

245
00:13:11,643 --> 00:13:13,077
-I think that all
things considered,

246
00:13:13,110 --> 00:13:15,143
his level of cooperation
is fine for now.

247
00:13:15,177 --> 00:13:20,377
And besides, I discovered
something very important.

248
00:13:20,410 --> 00:13:22,243
The person suspected
of being Kira

249
00:13:22,277 --> 00:13:25,610
is Deputy Director Yagami's son.

250
00:13:25,643 --> 00:13:27,677
